The paper discusses the use of a robotic snake for navigation in obstacle-strewn environments, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The use of a monocular color camera for visual processing and localization suggests computer vision (cs.CV) as another likely sub-category. The paper also mentions the need for resolving challenges related to perception and planning, which could fall under artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and control systems (cs.SY). Finally, the use of a simplified motion model and trajectory tracking suggests machine learning (cs.LG) as a possible sub-category.
